    <div class="section-title">
      <h2>About Little Worlds Workshop</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="about-text">
      <p>
        In the middle of our everyday full and busy lives, it can feel hard to engage with your child in a focused
        meaningful way.  We want to give them all of our attention while they tell us stories or invite us to play, but our
        attention is often pulled in a myriad of necessary directions.
      </p><p>
        Little Worlds workshop is here to help! Our classes are designed to create the space and time for you
        and your child to connect. Each class contains focused creative play time, a low pressure arts activity,
        and relaxation and mindfulness activities that you and your child do together. Every element of the workshop is
        designed to maximize the opportunities for you to simply enjoy the unique person that is your child.
      </p><p>
        The workshops are designed for pairs, one child (aged 4-7) and one parent. The emphasis of the class is on
        providing a positive space for you and your child to smile together and not on producing a “perfect” product.
        We encourage parents to follow the lead of the child during play and let themselves and their child enjoy the
        freedom of a moment designed to have fewer rules and expectations than many parts of our lives. Little Worlds
        is a safe, fun, and creative environment designed to allow you to do the thing you want to do the most, be 100%
        present with your kid.
      </p>
    </div>
